# Cursor Rule: Project Foundation

Applies To: Entire Repository

Priority: Highest

---

## Project

Project Name: PrivateConnect

Version: 1.0 MVP

Architecture: MERN Stack

Users Supported: 100

---

## Objective

Build a production-ready private communication platform.

The project must be modular, secure, maintainable, and fully documented.

---

## Core Stack

Frontend
* React
* Vite
* Tailwind CSS

Backend
* Node.js
* Express.js

Database
* MongoDB Atlas

Realtime
* Socket.io

Media
* WebRTC

Deployment
* Vercel
* Render

---

## Before Writing Code

Always read:
* docs/01_AI_MEMORY.md
* docs/03_PROJECT_RULES.md
* docs/19_PROJECT_PROGRESS.md
* docs/21_TODO.md

Never start implementation without checking project progress.

---

## Project Rules

Never change architecture without approval.
Never install unnecessary dependencies.
Never remove working code.
Never ignore documentation.
Never commit secrets.
Always update documentation after implementing a feature.

---

## Coding Rules

Use JavaScript.
Use functional React components.
Controllers must remain thin.
Business logic belongs in services.
Create reusable components.
Create reusable middleware.
Create reusable utilities.

---

## Security

Use JWT.
Hash Secret Codes.
Validate all input.
Enable Helmet.
Enable CORS.
Enable Rate Limiting.
Never expose sensitive data.

---

## MVP Scope

Allowed
* Secret Code Authentication
* Username Setup
* One-to-One Chat
* Voice Call
* Video Call
* Admin Dashboard

Not Allowed
* Group Chat
* Group Calls
* File Sharing
* Push Notifications
* Mobile Apps
* End-to-end Encryption

---

## End Of Every Task

Before finishing:
* Verify code compiles.
* Verify no obvious runtime errors.
* Update PROJECT_PROGRESS.md.
* Update CHANGELOG.md.
* Update TODO.md if necessary.
* Summarize implemented work.

This rule is mandatory.
